      "rationale": "N=11 constructs assembled from production-intent hardware (same lot as regulatory submission). Traceability records link each specimen to CMM measurement report and material certificate. Sample size exceeds ASTM F1717 minimum of N=5."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span the range of COU operating conditions, including at least two load levels or construct configurations to assess model response across the intended use envelope.",
      "rationale": "Testing was conducted under a single ASTM F1717 loading configuration at the nominal 40 mm offset. The protocol is well-established and widely accepted for regulatory submissions, and the inter-laboratory reproducibility across two independent test sites provides confidence in the experimental reference data. Environmental conditions (temperature, humidity) were controlled per ASTM F1717 requirements throughout."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA model inputs (geometry, material properties, boundary conditions) demonstrably equivalent to experimental test conditions.",
      "rationale": "FEA boundary conditions replicate ASTM F1717 fixture geometry (40 mm offset, fixed-fixed end conditions). Material properties matched to certified lot data used for test specimens. CMM-measured specimen geometry used to confirm nominal CAD dimensions within tolerance."
    },
